esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert on Kubernetes Node EvictionThresholdMet events.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Node under resource pressure — evicting pods to reclaim memory/disk/inodes.
//
// Common causes:
// Memory pressure, disk pressure, inode exhaustion, PID exhaustion.
//
// Action needed:
// Check node resources, scale cluster, adjust pod limits, investigate resource leaks.
//
// To scope to a cluster, add: AND `orchestrator.cluster.name` == "YOUR_CLUSTER"
FROM metrics-kubernetes.event-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.event.involved_object.kind` == "Node"
  AND `kubernetes.event.source.component` == "kubelet"
  AND `kubernetes.event.reason` == "EvictionThresholdMet"
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.event.involved_object.name`,
     `kubernetes.event.involved_object.kind`, `kubernetes.event.reason`
| WHERE doc_count > 0
